diff:1372654655:1372654655:=1,63d0%0a%3c (:title Werewolf Character Creation:)%0a%3c [[#wtop]]%0a%3c [[GameRef.WerewolfCharacterCreation?action=edit|Click here to Edit]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:table border=0 style=float width=40%25 align=right  cellspacing=0 :)%0a%3c (:cellnr align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr:)%0a%3c (:cellnr bgcolor=#996600 align=center:)%0a%3c '''Contents'''%0a%3c (:cellnr:) %0a%3c *[[#Creation| Character Creation]]%0a%3c *[[#Restricted| Restricted]]%0a%3c *[[#ixp| Incentive XP]]%0a%3c (:tableend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Creation]]%0a%3c [++'''Character Creation'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Unless explicitly stated otherwise, assume that the [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=250&t=32372|General Character Creation Guidelines]] are in effect.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Minimum Renown:''' Werewolves belonging to one of the Tribes must start with at least three total dots of Renown. Ghost Wolves must start with at least two total dots of Renown.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->This means purchasing at least one dot on top of your free Renown for Auspice & Tribe. Buying Renown at character creation does ''not'' give free Affinity Gifts.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Compulsory Gifts:''' Werewolves belonging to one of the Tribes must start with at least one level 1 Tribal Gift and one level 1 Auspice Gift. The exception to this is that if you have an overlapping List for your Tribe and Auspice (e.g. Storm Lords and Rahu both have access to the Dominance List, so this is an overlapping list for Storm Lord Rahu), you can choose the level 1 and 2 Gifts from this List instead.%0a%3c %0a%3c ->Ghost Wolves must start with at least one level 1 Auspice Gift.%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#996600%25[[#wtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Restricted]]%0a%3c [++'''Restricted List'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Please consult the [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=321&t=32346|O/R/B Book List]] to see what books you may draw material from.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Renown:''' Renown at 3 costs one restricted slot. You may not start with Renown at 4 or higher.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Rituals:''' Rituals 3 costs one restricted slot and is the maximum that starting characters may have, except Ithaeur; Ithaeur may start with up to Rituals 4, but this costs a total of two restricted slots.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Fetishes:''' Every new Fetish taken after the first one costs one restricted slot; otherwise, there are no special rules. ''Example: one level 3 Fetish is no restricted slots. One level 2 Fetish and one level 1 Fetish comes to 1 restricted slot.''%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Lodges:''' Characters who meet the pre-requisites may start on a Lodge; this requires one restricted slot.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Territory (including Locus), Totem & Pack Tactics:''' These are only available at creation to characters who start with a pack; if your character is packless, you must first join a pack and then acquire them.%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Other Merits:'''%0a%3c **'''Language (First Tongue):''' Werewolves who belong to a Tribe do not need this Merit; in other words, if you belong to a Tribe at character creation, but you forget to add this Merit to your sheet, it is still assumed your character can speak & write in the First Tongue. Ghost Wolves must still purchase it, however. (I'll admit that my motivation here is as much to save us STs the effort of post-sanction corrections as anything else... -MarcD)%0a%3c %0a%3c **'''Allies (Local Spirits), Contacts (Local Spirits), etc.:''' These are banned at character creation, but may be acquired IC.%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#996600%25[[#wtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#ixp]]%0a%3c [++'''Incentive XP'''++]\\%0a%3c You may gain a total of up to +10 Incentive XP at creation (+5 for General Incentive XP and +5 from Werewolf Incentive XP). See the guidelines here:%0a%3c *[[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=250&t=32374|General Incentive XP]]%0a%3c *[[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=454&t=34024|Werewolf Incentive XP]]%0a%3c %0a%3c To apply Incentive XP, simply go over the limit of General XP by that equivalent amount. For instance, if you are using 8 Incentive XP, go ahead and spend XP until you are at -8 General XP on your character sheet. ''You should be clear about why you think you deserve Incentive XP'': document what you are aiming to get the bonuses from in your Notes field.%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#996600%25[[#wtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:include CityBook.WerewolfNavigationBar:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
